Question: is hate generated by taunt cumulative?<br>
<br>
I.e. Will hitting taunt 2 or 3 times before waking a mezzed mob make it more likely not to run after Enc?<br>
If so, will hitting taunt through out a fight make a mob less likely to switch targets?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=anduvar>Anduvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 12:53 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://kair.50megs.com/anduhead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunt query</span><hr size=1> A successful taunt simply places you at the top of the hate list.  It does not have a cumulative effect.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Anduvar Du'Rai<br>
Myrmidon of Norrath<br>
Companions of the Gate<br>
Bristlebane Server</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
View Anduvar's Magelo Profile <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103734">HERE</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dwelfnvhal>DwelfnVhal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/03 12:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunt query</span><hr size=1> Nope Jimjam. Taunt takes you to just above the previous highest aggro player (although no accurate figures on how much is added on top can be obtained, the amount (if there is any) is basically negligable). <br>
<br>
The reason for hitting taunt multiple times is that taunt doesn't work every time, by hitting it 2-3 times a warrior is edging the odds of a successful taunt in his favour. <br>
<br>
An alternative mentioned here just recently is to /assist the mob after each taunt to see if he has you targetted (indicating a successful taunt) I'll have to try that myself heh.<br>
<br>
Oh, and the search button is your friend <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
